Step 1: Determine the Owner's Equity at the beginning and the ending of the period.  
• Beginning Owner's Equity (paid-in capital on 2023-12-31): 13,000,000.00  
• Ending Owner's Equity (2024-01-28): 14,105,265.77  

Step 2: Calculate the Average Owner's Equity.  
Average Owner's Equity = (Beginning Owner’s Equity + Ending Owner’s Equity) / 2  
= (13,000,000.00 + 14,105,265.77) / 2  
= 27,105,265.77 / 2  
≈ 13,552,632.89  

Step 3: Obtain the Net Profit from the Income Statement.  
Net Profit = 1,105,265.77  

Step 4: Calculate ROE (Return on Equity) using the formula:  
ROE = (Net Profit / Average Owner’s Equity) × 100%  
≈ (1,105,265.77 / 13,552,632.89) × 100%  
≈ 0.08157 × 100%  
≈ 8.16%

Thus, the ROE is approximately 8.16%.
